---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const missionStatements = [
    "To regenerate soil health through holistic grazing practices that mimic nature's patterns",
    "To raise animals humanely, allowing them to express their natural behaviors on open pasture",
    "To produce nutrient-dense food without synthetic chemicals or harmful inputs",
    "To serve as stewards of the land, enhancing biodiversity and ecosystem resilience",
    "To connect our community directly to sustainable food systems through transparency and education",
];
---

<Layout>
    <header slot="header">
        <h1>At The Holt Farms</h1>
        <p>A small farm that Raises Pastured Protein</p>
        <a href="/future-plans">whats on the farm</a>
    </header>
    <main slot="main">
        <section>
            <h2>What is Raising Pastured Protein</h2>
            <p>
                We raise sheep and chickens on healthy pastures using
                regenerative practices that heal the land while producing
                exceptionally nutritious food.
            </p>
            <a href="/future-plans"> Learn more about our future plans </a>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h3>Farming background</h3>
            <p>
                I grew up on a Dairy farm so livestock has always been a part of
                my life. I have had few flocks of chickens a couple of goats and
                a few cows and one rabbit. Mostly just as a hobby and joy having
                livestock around the house. There was a dry spell prior to 2022,
                then early that year is when we had the opportunity to bottle
                feed a couple of Rams. We had them in the house for a bit, the
                kiddos had a real laugh with the lambs running through the
                dinning room. Pastures where established and they where traded
                for a few ewes and now a flock of 12. Year of 2025 we are adding
                the largest heritage chicken the Jersey Giants.
            </p>
            <a href="animals/">Our Animals</a>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h3>Reasons why to raise pasture protein</h3>
            <p>
                In 2015 one of children was diagnosed with brain cancer which
                lead us down a road of researching what was in our food and
                wanting to provide my family with good quality food. Also the to
                fight the industrialization of our food, I don't believe that
                animal are designed to be feed a diet that will grow them
                quickest, I believe that we are here to work with nature not to
                bend to what suits us.
            </p>
            <a href="resources/">Information on Regenerated Agriculture</a>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h3>Main Goals for farm</h3>
            <p>
                To provide high quality pasture raised meat and eggs to our
                community. By giving livestock the nutrients they were designed
                to eat,and ensure their health and well-being come first. Give
                the land time to rest and regenerate, by implement regenerative
                practices.
            </p>
            <a href="resources/">Information on Regenerated Agriculture</a>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h3>Mission Statements</h3>
            <ul>
                {missionStatements.map((x) => <li>{x}</li>)}
            </ul>
        </section>
    </main>
</Layout>

<style>
    header {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        justify-content: center;
        align-items: center;
        width: 100%;
        padding: 50px;
    }
    h2,
    h3 {
        text-align: center;
    }
    section {
        margin: 10px 0px;
    }
</style>
